rComments: Connaît bien sa matière mais n'a jamais respecté le plan de cours. Nous avons seulement vu 1/4 de la matière en classe. Ses exigences ne sont pas claires en ce qui a trait au travail de session et des examens.
Wonderful Prof. Interesting course, she knows her material very well. Recommend her course.
Wonderful Prof. I would recommend her courses for sure.

She is a terrific teacher for this border and migration subject,she is so helpful and nice,her expectations for midterm are clear,her grades are pretty good.I would recommend to have a course with her for sure. Despite her French heavy accent, she delivers the information in a professional academic manner.

I did not like this teacher. She reads off the slides and does not stimulate class discussion. You end up sitting through the whole class staring a slideshows while she reads off the slides. Did not give sufficient respect to her students. Often verbally expresses that she assumes that students will plagiarize, and that they are lazy.

Very good teacher. The level is not always as high as i would have liked, but obviously she tries to level with the class. She's very helpfull and nice if you have to speak with her. She obviously knows very well what she teaches.

Explanations very confusing, however she will clarify a little if you ask. She speaks very quickly, repeats herself often while constantly staring at her notes. She's very slow compared to the readings she assigned. On the first midterm we viewed three chapters in class but have been assigned eight to read.

A typical amount of pedanticism for a third year class; however, the myriad of abstract concepts are delivered through chopped sentences, an incoherent french accent, and a prof who only stares at her notes for an hour and a half straight. Very difficult to follow lectures.

Interesting course, however the professor could have been more engaging. She reads directly off the slides and follows the readings closely. This professor does not post slides online so attendance is crucial. Midterm and final are fairly easy if you study sufficiently. The exam questions only covered the most well known IOs (i.e league of nations)
